18.81	Johnson_Beharry	Johnson Beharry	Lance Corporal Johnson Gideon Beharry VC (born 26 July 1979)) of the 1st Battalion, Princess of Wales's Royal Regiment, is a British Army soldier who, on 18 March 2005, was awarded the Victoria Cross, the highest military decoration for valour in the British and Commonwealth armed forces, for twice saving members of his unit from ambushes on 1 May and again on 11 June 2004 at Al-Amarah, Iraq. He sustained serious head injuries in the latter engagement. Beharry was formally invested with the Victoria Cross by Queen Elizabeth II on 27 April 2005.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/03/Johnson_Beharry%2C_VC.jpg/200px-Johnson_Beharry%2C_VC.jpg
